-- Global Funds Buy Net 458 Million Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-09-10T04:05:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/global-funds-buy-net-458-million-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  bought a  net 458
million rupees ($8.3 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  in a
special trading session on Sept. 8, according to the National
Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, was at 776.4 billion rupees, according to the
exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 194 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Sept. 8, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
